{"lemma":"شَرَطُ","slug":"شَرَطُ","root":"ش.ر.ط","root_slug":"ش-ر-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n22118","n22119"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make a condition, to stipulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make incisions in the skin, to scarify"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fasten with a string of palm bast"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tear into pieces","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to scarify, to cup"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make small chains or rosaries","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَرَطَ (šaraṭa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"condition, reservation, proviso, stipulation, article of a compact, contract, requirement, prescription, obligation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"incision, scarification"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"low, mean"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of شَرِيط (šarīṭ)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of شُرْطَة (šurṭa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃu.ratˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22118","headword_ar":"شَرْطٌ","root":"$rT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A condition; a term; a stipulation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said to signify] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imposition of a thing as obligatory"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a person"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking it upon oneself as such, in a sale and the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) [but this is a loose explanation, as is observed in the TK; the meaning being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing imposed upon a person as obligatory, and taken upon oneself as such:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the S, it is merely said to be well known:] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyTapN","text_ar":"شَرِيطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (S, Msb, K:) pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwTN","text_ar":"شُرُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) and of the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAy^iTu","text_ar":"شَرَايِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yajuwzu","text_ar":"لَا يَجُوزُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroTaAni fiY bayoEK","text_ar":"شَرْطَانِ فِى بَيْعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two conditions in a sale are not allowable"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as when one says, “ I sell to thee this garment, or piece of cloth, for ready money for a deenár, and on credit for two deenárs. ” (TA.) And it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aroTu A^amolaku Ealayoka A^amo laka","text_ar":"الشَّرْطُ اَمْلَكُ عَلَيْكَ اَمْ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The condition is most valid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[whether it be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against thee or in thy favour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mlk","text_ar":"ملك"},{"kind":"text","text":":) relating to the keeping of conditions between brothers. (Sgh, TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroTN","text_ar":"شَرْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also relates to other things beside sales and the like: for instance, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroTu AlmaSodari ka*aA waka*aA","text_ar":"شَرْطُ المَصْدَرِ كَذَا وَكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is required to justify the application of the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mSdr","text_ar":"مصدر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is such a thing, and such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroTaA nahorK","text_ar":"شَرْطَا نَهْرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two banks of a river."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [The pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwTN","text_ar":"شُرُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Roads leading in different directions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araTN","text_ar":"شَرَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22119","headword_ar":"شَرَطٌ","root":"$rT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign, token,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which men appoint between them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroTN","text_ar":"شَرْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraATN","text_ar":"اَشْرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.) And hence, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraATu Als~aAEapi","text_ar":"اَشْرَاطُ السَّاعَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The signs of the resurrection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the time thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA;) mentioned in the Kur [xlvii. 20]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the small events prior thereto, which men deny:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Khattábee:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the means thereof, exclusive of the main circumstances thereof, and of the event itself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~araTaAni","text_ar":"الشَّرَطَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"b]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are the two horns of Aries;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, Kzw;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the brighter whereof is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aATiHu","text_ar":"النَّاطِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Kzw;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the other,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aToHu","text_ar":"النَّطْحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the First Mansion of the Moon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw:) to-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wards the north of them is a small star which some of the Arabs reckon with those two, saying that it"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"namely this mansion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consists of three stars, and calling them"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^a$oraATu","text_ar":"الاَشْرَاطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) IAar mentions an instance of the use of the sing.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~araTu","text_ar":"الشَّرَطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the dual is more approved, and more commonly known: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two stars above mentioned are the first asterism of the spring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, Z.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAzilu Alqamari","text_ar":"مَنَازِلُ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzl","text_ar":"نزل"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hassán Ibn-Thábit says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fiY nadaAmaY biyDi Alwujuwhi kiraAmK\n                      \n                     \n                        nub~ihuwA baEoda hajoEapi AlA^a$oraATi"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Among fair-faced, generous cup-companions, roused from sleep after"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the setting of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$rAT","text_ar":"اشراط"},{"kind":"text","text":": though another meaning, which see below, has been assigned to the last word. (Sgh.) ―         -b3-  And hence, (ISd, Z,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araTN","text_ar":"شَرَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beginning"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (ISd, * Z, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi$oraATN","text_ar":"مِشْرَاطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ibn-'Abbád, K:) pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraATN","text_ar":"اَشْرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beginnings"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any event that happens because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araTaAn","text_ar":"شَرَطَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the first asterism of the spring: (ISd, Z:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m$rAT","text_ar":"مشراط","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense here expl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAriyTu","text_ar":"مَشَارِيطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) Hence, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraATu Als~aAEapi","text_ar":"اَشْرَاطُ السَّاعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. above. (TA.)       -A2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as the galled in the back, and the emaciated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd,) of camels or the like, (S, K,) or of goats, (Msb,) or of goats also: (S:) used alike as sing. and pl. and masc. and fem.: and applied particularly to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels, as a pl. and as a sing.: also, to a she-camel and to a he-camel: and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as is brought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"driven, from one place to another for sale; as the aged she-camel, and the camel that is galled in the back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also the same, not ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroTN","text_ar":"شَرْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the K, [without restriction of its application,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low, base, vile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraTu","text_ar":"اَشْرَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraATN","text_ar":"اَشْرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAriyTu","text_ar":"اَشَارِيطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S,* TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alganamu","text_ar":"الغَنَمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraATu AlmaAli","text_ar":"اَشْرَاطُ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, are the refuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest sort, of beasts that people possess"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araTN","text_ar":"شَرَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to men; (S, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araTu","text_ar":"شَرَطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The refuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest sort, pf mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) In the verse of Hassán Ibn-Thábit cited above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^a$oraAT","text_ar":"الاَشْرَاط"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The guards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watchmen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lowest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest sort of people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Sgh;) [so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajoEap","text_ar":"هَجْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"must be understood in the sense of “ a light sleep in the first part of the night; ”] but the correct meaning is that expl. before. (Sgh.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraATN","text_ar":"اَشْرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honourable, sort"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men: thus the word has two contr. significations. (Yaakoob, S, K.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small water-course coming from a space of ten cubits:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what flows from even tracts of ground into the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"larger water-courses called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEaAb","text_ar":"شِعَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Kzw","ISd","Z","AHn","O"]}]}}